column3:
If escaping social media isn't an option, at least make it something that brings you up and doesn't tear you down!

#healthysocialmedia #loveeachother #selfcare #socialmediaanxiety #Ruthere

Have you noticed your vision worsening? Or a lack of motivation? These symptoms may be related to excessive screen time. Check out this article for more information on the potential repercussions of your technology use. #RUThere #WisdomWednesday

https://health.usf.edu/is/blog/2018/06/26/technologys-effect-on-our-health-the-good-the-bad-and-the-ugly

Happiness comes from inner peace, not likes and comments.

#socialmediaanxiety #healthysocialmedia #selfcare #metime #Ruthere

The only person who needs to think you're doing well - is YOU!

#mentalhealth #socialmediaanxiety #metime #CheckOnYou #loveyourself #Ruthere

Quick reminder to take a second and check back in!

#mentalhealth #socialmediaanxiety #CheckOnYou #metime #socialmedia #Ruthere

We post what we want others to see, not necessarily the reality.

#socialmediaanxiety #CheckOnYou #selfcare #peaceful #realYOU #Ruthere

Don't forget to pay attention to how the REAL you is feeling!

#socialmediaanxiety #mentalhealth #socialmedia #Ruthere

Need a break from social media? Imagine if your job was centred around social media, how would you escape from it? Celine Hoffman, a social media manager, describes her struggle with balancing her job and social media addiction. 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YPzfGi8fZc0&feature=youtu.be

#socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth #metime #selfcare

Teens these days are more likely to be a passive engager from watching others on social media. Take control of your time and be conscious of your social media use. 

#RUThere #MindfulMondays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OnGZ28pviOM

Have technology work for you. Track what you eat and accomplish your health and dieting goals. Check out these awesome apps!

#RUThere #SelfcareSundays #metime #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/health-products/g28245675/best-food-tracking-apps/

"I've tried to be super conscious about my social media use since I've been in college. I personally feel like it's too easy to get sucked into this spiral of scrolling. I love all of the ways in which my phone lets me connect to others, but it also impedes spending time with friends; I often find myself sitting with four or five friends and everyone will be silently staring at their phones scrolling. I've used the 'Screen Time' settings on my phone to help me be aware and cut down on the time I spend on certain apps, and I've had success with it." - Scott Gelb

#RUThere #FeatureFridays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

Internet addicts may have similar changes in their brain chemistry to that of a drug addict study finds. Are you spending too much time on social media today? Take a break. 

#RUThere #WisdomWednesday #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0030253#s4

We can continue to leverage our smartphones to improve healthcare. Watch Dr. Mohammed Dalwai talk about how we can move forward and make healthcare more accessible. 

#RUThere #MindfulMondays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-7ozuI1tt8

A number of apps can help in moments where you are considering self-harm. Consider free apps like Calm Harm that give various ways to help, from distraction to comfort to so much more. Explore some options in the link below. 

#RUThere #SelfcareSundays #metime #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://vitals.lifehacker.com/get-through-an-urge-to-self-harm-with-these-apps-1822307711

3 or more hours a day on social media can negatively impact your mental health, study finds. The next time you open social media, think about how much you've used it that day. 

#Ruthere #WisdomWednesdays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/the-big-number-3-or-more-hours-a-day-of-social-media-use-hurts-youths-mental-health/2019/09/27/043c7dc0-e06f-11e9-8dc8-498eabc129a0_story.html

How Social Media Makes Us More Unsocial - This Ted talk examines how the platforms we depend on to keep us connected to one another, actually keep us apart.

#Ruthere #MindfulMondays

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d5GecYjy9-Q

Sometimes we don't have the option to put down our devices, especially considering we do most of our work on them! 

Here are a few apps to help you regain control of your thoughts when you feel like everything is happening a little too quickly.

#Ruthere #SelfcareSundays #metime #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.mindful.org/free-mindfulness-apps-worthy-of-your-attention/

"I actually went on a social media cleanse recently. I feel like I needed a break because it was putting a lot of extra stress on my life that I didn’t need. After two days I got it back, and I think that just shows how people have an insane dependence on social media. When you don’t have it, your life is a lot more calm because you’re not worried about what other people are doing, and it’s an easier way to focus on yourself. I want to try and have more social media cleanses in the future because I do think it affected me positively, but it’s something I need to work on." –Dianella Jaguan 

#Ruthere #FeatureFridays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

Looking for a job? 

A study reveals that 43 percent of hiring managers, who research candidates on social media, said they have found information causing them not to hire a candidate. Be aware of the longterm impacts your posts can have, and think about whether you want your boss to see that post 

#Ruthere #WisdomWednesdays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.careerbuilder.com/share/aboutus/pressreleasesdetail.aspx?ed=12%2F31%2F2013&id=pr766&sd=6%2F26%2F2013

In a society in which we can't escape technology, doctors are encouraging socially anxious patients to take control of social media before it takes over them.

This article dives into the ways doctors are treating patients. Rather than feeding into their social media anxiety by keeping them away from it, they encourage them to post, share and interact with others. With technology advancing, if people are not in tune with the the internet, they'll soon be out of touch with the rest of the world. 

#Ruthere #MindfulMondays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.wsj.com/articles/when-the-prescription-for-teens-is-more-social-media-not-less-11572276260?mod=hp_lead_pos10

Do you know how your social media use is affecting your body? Watch this quick AsapSCIENCE video to learn how your body deals with multitasking and why social media use releases dopamine 

#MindfulMondays #Ruthere #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HffWFd_6bJ0

Keep your brain cognition sharp with fun apps like Lumosity: Daily Brain Games, which help you gain knowledge and think critically. Technology, when used well, can be one of your greatest assets 

#Ruthere  #SelfcareSundays #metime #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.lumosity.com/en/

"Social Media has both positively and negatively impacted me. Instagram helps inspire me. I like to look up various food-related Instagram accounts and get ideas for new recipes. Facebook has helped me to stay connected, create events, publicize the shows I produced, and even network. On the other hand, I probably spend too much time on Facebook, which definitely impacts my productivity. I also get most of my news from links I find on Facebook. Although I always am aware of what source I get my news from and question its validity, my worldview is probably narrowed because Facebook algorithms must be feeding me a select collection of information." — Jonathan Gelb 

#Ruthere #FeatureFridays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

Feel free to skim this longer read that goes into the quirks and pitfalls of growing up with tech.

"I try to put a lot of energy into being present everyday, but phones and social media can often draw me away from the moment that I’m in. In some situations, I’ll be having a conversation with a friend or classmate while they are checking their phone. Staying plugged into the world around you is important as your phone can be the doorway to maintaining punctuality, discovering opportunities, and growing your sphere of knowledge, but when the phone begins taking up space in a face to face conversation it can be detrimental. I often feel ignored and unimportant when someone focuses on their phone more than me, especially in conversations." — Nyla Smith 

#Ruthere #FeatureFridays #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

Boredom can be beneficial in that it motivates you. With technology being more pervasive than ever, consider when you are using technology to combat your boredom, and try to pivot to something more beneficial and productive for yourself. 

#WisdomWednesdays #Ruthere #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TYX8B122EmU

According to a 2019 national survey, there has been a sharp increase in the number of young adults and adolescents who reported experiencing negative psychological symptoms, affecting primarily those born after 1995. Reflect today on how social media and technology impact your mental health.

#WisdomWednesdays #Ruthere #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth

https://www.nbcnews.com/health/mental-health/social-media-linked-rise-mental-health-disorders-teens-survey-finds-n982526

R u there? is a page dedicated to raising awareness for the danger that social media and technology pose to mental health. People are growing increasingly disconnected from one another and are becoming more dependent on technology when forming their own identity. Our goal is not turn you off from social media, but rather, to introduce tips to reenforce healthy boundaries between you and your online self. We want you to be present in your life. We want to know if you are there.

#Ruthere #socialmedia #socialworld #mentalhealth
